From: OpenWrt HA build <local>
Subject: [PATCH] lease-sync: handle DHCPv6 identity without MAC ping-pong

DHCPv6 leases are identified by client-id/DUID plus IAID, not by an IPv4-style
MAC address. Treat DHCPv6 identity separately from IPv4 MAC conflict handling,
reject incomplete DHCPv6 peer/local events, and resolve duplicate DHCPv6
identity leases deterministically so two nodes do not keep replacing each
other's addresses.

Also write short-lived suppression markers before daemon-initiated dnsmasq
add_lease/delete_lease calls. The hotplug script consumes these markers before
publishing, so reflected add/update/delete events are dropped before they can
be re-emitted to peers.

